article.headline: ETSU 72, Jacksonville 58
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- Adam Sollazzo had 18 points to pace four East Tennessee State players in double-figure scoring as the Buccaneers beat Jacksonville 72-58 on Saturday. Tommy Hubbard scored 16 points, Isiah Brown 13 and Sheldon Cooley 11 for ETSU (9-7, 4-2 Atlantic Sun Conference), which has now won a season-high four games in a row. In the first half, ETSU led just 15-14 with 12 minutes left before the break, but closed out the first 20 minutes on a 23-5 run to take a 38-19 lead into the locker room. In the second half, ETSU led by as many as 21 points at 60-39 with 8:38 left. Aloys Cabell, Evin Graham and Keith McDougald each had 10 points to lead the Dolphins (2-15, 0-6). The loss stretched Jacksonville's losing streak to a season-high 13 games, starting with a 107-62 loss to No. 19 Florida on Nov. 25.
